.TH "xudc_start_dma" 9 "xudc_start_dma" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
xudc_start_dma \- Starts DMA transfer.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" xudc_start_dma
.BI "(struct xusb_ep *ep "  ","
.BI "dma_addr_t src "  ","
.BI "dma_addr_t dst "  ","
.BI "u32 length "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ep" 12
pointer to the usb device endpoint structure.
.IP "src" 12
DMA source address.
.IP "dst" 12
DMA destination address.
.IP "length" 12
number of bytes to transfer.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, error code on failure
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function starts DMA transfer by writing to DMA source,
destination and lenth registers.
